<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="712" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1800.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to
                                    Chile</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-16"><hi rend="italic">May 16,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Chilean minister to Mexico telegraphs the minister for foreign
                            affairs that it seems likely the revolution will succeed, and requests
                            authority to lend his good offices should an opportunity to mediate
                            offer. The minister for foreign affairs stated that such mediation will
                            not be authorized unless perfectly acceptable to the United States. The
                            Chilean chargé d’affaires, upon my suggestion, has been instructed by
                            telegraph to ascertain the Department’s views.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
